    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        SHEET METAL REPAIRS - TOOLS AND MATERIALS REQUIRED
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>TOOLS AND MATERIALS REQUIRED</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">3/8 inch Electric or Pneumatic drill, assorted drill bits and sheet metal drill bit.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">MIG or Heliarc Welder with aluminum weld wire (Spec. No. 4043).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Electric, Pneumatic or Hydraulic Riveter. Since there are different types of fasteners used
                in the construction of the riveted cab, the proper installation tool must be used. Approved tools are
                listed in
                <hotlnk xrefid="hl1600618">Table 1</hotlnk>
                below.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">There is an assortment of fasteners with various grip ranges (total thickness of materials
                being fastened). See
                <hotlnk xrefid="hl1600619">Table 2</hotlnk>
                for required fasteners.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <para>Refer to parts catalog for fastener part numbers. Descriptions of fasteners are outlined under
            <hotlnk document="s16006_42.xml" xrefid="hl1600620">TYPES OF PANEL FASTENERS
                <xref refid="hl1600620"/>
            </hotlnk>
            .
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Because of the superior clamping ability of the "pin and collar" (Lockbolt) type fastener (
                    <hotlnk document="s16006_42.xml" xrefid="f1600652">Figure 52</hotlnk>), Lockbolts must be used
                    whenever access permits.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
