        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>In lieu of Lockbolt accessibility, a 1/4 inch (6.35mm) Monobolt type fastener (
                    <hotlnk document="s16006_42.xml" xrefid="f1600653">Figure 53</hotlnk>) should be used.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Specific locations (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600654">Figure 54</hotlnk>) require use of a special 1/4 inch "Cherry G" rivet to
                    assure positive clamping.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1600654" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1600652" filename="../figg16/G1600652.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 52. Locations of 1/4 Inch (6.35mm) "Cherry G" Rivets</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. "A" PILLAR-TO-ROOF (3 RIVETS)</callout1>
                <callout1>2. "A" PILLAR-TO-FRONT CORNER PANEL (3 RIVETS)</callout1>
                <callout1>3. ROCKER PANEL-TO-FRONT CORNER PANEL (4 RIVETS)</callout1>
                <callout1>4. UPPER REAR DOOR OPENING FILLER-TO-LOCK PILLAR AND HEADER (5 RIVETS)</callout1>
                <callout1>5. ROCKER PANEL REAR-TO-LOWER LOCK PILLAR (4 RIVETS)</callout1>
                <callout1>6. ROCKER PANEL-TO-DOOR OPENING FRAME INSIDE SURFACE (INDICATED BY ARROW) (1 RIVET)</callout1>
                <callout1>7. FRONT CENTER PANEL-TO-FRONT CORNER PANEL (3 RIVETS EACH SIDE)</callout1>
                <callout1>8. CAB REAR PANEL-TO-REAR LOWER PANEL (6 RIVETS EACH SIDE)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>To avoid repeated loosening of rivets, it is imperative that the proper tools and procedures, as
                    outlined herein, are adhered to. DO NOT USE "POP-RIVETS." They do not have sufficient clamping
                    ability for these types of repairs.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Use rivets of the same material (aluminum) you are fastening. The inter-mixing of materials
                    invites corrosion and possible rivet failure unless anti-corrosion measures are taken.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
